obo:GO_0098839  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_5399  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2: in biochemical fractions prepared from mice forebrain, Slack (KCTN1) was enriched in PSD fractions. Staining was abolished in Slack knockout mice.\n\nFigure 2, 3: Infant Slack-/- show reduced NMDAR-mediated transmission and lack mGluR LTD.\n\nFigure 4: Slack-/- deficiency impairs dephosphorylation of GluA1 S845 after LTD induction.\n\nFigure 5: NMDAR-dependent LTD but not LTP is impaired in adult Slack-/-.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Subcellular fractionation was performed as described earlier [35]. Seven whole forebrains were pooled from P9 and 4-8 hippocampi from adult Slack+/+ or Slack-/- mice. \"\n\nantibody:\nanti-Slack, NeuroMab, 75-051, mouse IgG1" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5399" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

